<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900613-0144</DOCNO><DOCID>900613-0144.</DOCID><HL>   Litton Gear Picked by Carriers</HL><DATE>06/13/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   LIT F.AFR F.UTA</CO><IN>AIRLINES (AIR)</IN><LP>   BEVERLY HILLS, Calif. -- Litton Industries Inc. said twoFrench airlines, UTA and Air France, have selected its newlaser gyro inertial navigation system for their future fleetsof Airbus Industrie A-340 aircraft. Financial terms weren'tdisclosed.   The airlines are scheduled to take delivery of theaircraft beginning in October 1992, and each of thesejetliners built by the European aircraft consortium will beequipped with three of the navigation systems, known asFlagship, and associated equipment.</LP><TEXT/></DOC>